members.name: getLocation
members.comment: Gets the entity's current position

return: a new copy of Location containing the position of this entity

members.name: getLocation
members.comment: Stores the entity's current position in the provided Location object. If the provided Location is null this method does nothing and returns null.

return: The Location object provided or null

members.name: setVelocity
members.comment: Sets this entity's velocity in meters per tick

members.name: getVelocity
members.comment: Gets this entity's current velocity

return: Current traveling velocity of this entity

members.name: getHeight
members.comment: Gets the entity's height

members.name: getWidth
members.comment: Gets the entity's width

members.name: getBoundingBox
members.comment: Gets the entity's current bounding box. The returned bounding box reflects the entity's current location and size.

members.name: isOnGround
members.comment: Returns true if the entity is supported by a block. This value is a state updated by the server and is not recalculated unless the entity moves.

return: True if entity is on ground.

members.name: isInWater
members.comment: Returns true if the entity is in water.

return: true if the entity is in water.

members.name: getWorld
members.comment: Gets the current world this entity resides in

members.name: setRotation
members.comment: Sets the entity's rotation. Note that if the entity is affected by AI, it may override this rotation.

throws: UnsupportedOperationException - if used for players

members.name: teleport
members.comment: Teleports this entity to the given location. If this entity is riding a vehicle, it will be dismounted prior to teleportation.

param: location - New location to teleport this entity to

members.name: teleport
members.comment: Teleports this entity to the given location. If this entity is riding a vehicle, it will be dismounted prior to teleportation.

param: location - New location to teleport this entity to

members.name: teleport
members.comment: Teleports this entity to the target Entity. If this entity is riding a vehicle, it will be dismounted prior to teleportation.

param: destination - Entity to teleport this entity to

members.name: teleport
members.comment: Teleports this entity to the target Entity. If this entity is riding a vehicle, it will be dismounted prior to teleportation.

param: destination - Entity to teleport this entity to

members.name: getNearbyEntities
members.comment: Returns a list of entities within a bounding box centered around this entity

param: x - 1/2 the size of the box along x axis
y - 1/2 the size of the box along y axis
z - 1/2 the size of the box along z axis

members.name: getEntityId
members.comment: Returns a unique id for this entity

members.name: getFireTicks
members.comment: Returns the entity's current fire ticks (ticks before the entity stops being on fire).

members.name: getMaxFireTicks
members.comment: Returns the entity's maximum fire ticks.

members.name: setFireTicks
members.comment: Sets the entity's current fire ticks (ticks before the entity stops being on fire).

members.name: setVisualFire
members.comment: Sets if the entity has visual fire (it will always appear to be on fire).

members.name: isVisualFire
members.comment: Gets if the entity has visual fire (it will always appear to be on fire).

members.name: getFreezeTicks
members.comment: Returns the entity's current freeze ticks (amount of ticks the entity has been in powdered snow).

members.name: getMaxFreezeTicks
members.comment: Returns the entity's maximum freeze ticks (amount of ticks before it will be fully frozen)

members.name: setFreezeTicks
members.comment: Sets the entity's current freeze ticks (amount of ticks the entity has been in powdered snow).

members.name: isFrozen
members.comment: Gets if the entity is fully frozen (it has been in powdered snow for max freeze ticks).

members.name: remove
members.comment: Mark the entity's removal.

members.name: isDead
members.comment: Returns true if this entity has been marked for removal.

members.name: isValid
members.comment: Returns false if the entity has died or been despawned for some other reason.

members.name: getServer
members.comment: Gets the Server that contains this Entity

members.name: isPersistent
members.comment: Returns true if the entity gets persisted. By default all entities are persistent. An entity will also not get persisted, if it is riding an entity that is not persistent. The persistent flag on players controls whether or not to save their playerdata file when they quit. If a player is directly or indirectly riding a non-persistent entity, the vehicle at the root and all its passengers won't get persisted. This should not be confused with LivingEntity.setRemoveWhenFarAway(boolean) which controls despawning of living entities.

return: true if this entity is persistent

members.name: setPersistent
members.comment: Sets whether or not the entity gets persisted.

members.name: getPassenger
members.comment: Gets the primary passenger of a vehicle. For vehicles that could have multiple passengers, this will only return the primary passenger.

members.name: setPassenger
members.comment: Set the passenger of a vehicle.

return: false if it could not be done for whatever reason

members.name: getPassengers
members.comment: Gets a list of passengers of this vehicle. The returned list will not be directly linked to the entity's current passengers, and no guarantees are made as to its mutability.

return: list of entities corresponding to current passengers.

members.name: addPassenger
members.comment: Add a passenger to the vehicle.

return: false if it could not be done for whatever reason

members.name: removePassenger
members.comment: Remove a passenger from the vehicle.

return: false if it could not be done for whatever reason

members.name: isEmpty
members.comment: Check if a vehicle has passengers.

return: True if the vehicle has no passengers.

members.name: eject
members.comment: Eject any passenger.

return: True if there was a passenger.

members.name: getFallDistance
members.comment: Returns the distance this entity has fallen

members.name: setFallDistance
members.comment: Sets the fall distance for this entity

members.name: setLastDamageCause
members.comment: Record the last EntityDamageEvent inflicted on this entity

members.name: getLastDamageCause
members.comment: Retrieve the last EntityDamageEvent inflicted on this entity. This event may have been cancelled.

return: the last known EntityDamageEvent or null if hitherto unharmed

members.name: getUniqueId
members.comment: Returns a unique and persistent id for this entity

members.name: getTicksLived
members.comment: Gets the amount of ticks this entity has lived for. This is the equivalent to "age" in entities.

members.name: setTicksLived
members.comment: Sets the amount of ticks this entity has lived for. This is the equivalent to "age" in entities. May not be less than one tick.

members.name: playEffect
members.comment: Performs the specified EntityEffect for this entity. This will be viewable to all players near the entity. If the effect is not applicable to this class of entity, it will not play.

members.name: getType
members.comment: Get the type of the entity.

members.name: isInsideVehicle
members.comment: Returns whether this entity is inside a vehicle.

return: True if the entity is in a vehicle.

members.name: leaveVehicle
members.comment: Leave the current vehicle. If the entity is currently in a vehicle (and is removed from it), true will be returned, otherwise false will be returned.

return: True if the entity was in a vehicle.

members.name: getVehicle
members.comment: Get the vehicle that this player is inside. If there is no vehicle, null will be returned.

members.name: setCustomNameVisible
members.comment: Sets whether or not to display the mob's custom name client side. The name will be displayed above the mob similarly to a player. This value has no effect on players, they will always display their name.

members.name: isCustomNameVisible
members.comment: Gets whether or not the mob's custom name is displayed client side. This value has no effect on players, they will always display their name.

return: if the custom name is displayed

members.name: setGlowing
members.comment: Sets whether the entity has a team colored (default: white) glow. nb: this refers to the 'Glowing' entity property, not whether a glowing potion effect is applied

members.name: isGlowing
members.comment: Gets whether the entity is glowing or not. nb: this refers to the 'Glowing' entity property, not whether a glowing potion effect is applied

members.name: setInvulnerable
members.comment: Sets whether the entity is invulnerable or not. When an entity is invulnerable it can only be damaged by players in creative mode.

members.name: isInvulnerable
members.comment: Gets whether the entity is invulnerable or not.

members.name: isSilent
members.comment: Gets whether the entity is silent or not.

members.name: setSilent
members.comment: Sets whether the entity is silent or not. When an entity is silent it will not produce any sound.

members.name: hasGravity
members.comment: Returns whether gravity applies to this entity.

members.name: setGravity
members.comment: Sets whether gravity applies to this entity.

members.name: getPortalCooldown
members.comment: Gets the period of time (in ticks) before this entity can use a portal.

members.name: setPortalCooldown
members.comment: Sets the period of time (in ticks) before this entity can use a portal.

members.name: getScoreboardTags
members.comment: Returns a set of tags for this entity. Entities can have no more than 1024 tags.

return: a set of tags for this entity

members.name: addScoreboardTag
members.comment: Add a tag to this entity. Entities can have no more than 1024 tags.

return: true if the tag was successfully added

members.name: removeScoreboardTag
members.comment: Removes a given tag from this entity.

return: true if the tag was successfully removed

members.name: getPistonMoveReaction
members.comment: Returns the reaction of the entity when moved by a piston.

members.name: getFacing
members.comment: Get the closest cardinal BlockFace direction an entity is currently facing. This will not return any non-cardinal directions such as BlockFace.UP or BlockFace.DOWN. Hanging entities will override this call and thus their behavior may be different.

members.name: getPose
members.comment: Gets the entity's current pose. Note that the pose is only updated at the end of a tick, so may be inconsistent with other methods. eg Player.isSneaking() being true does not imply the current pose will be Pose.SNEAKING
